<subSubSection id="C3150AD1FF89FFC3ECDE45E1B178FD18" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB0595AFF89FFC3ECDE45E1B0D6FDD5" blockId="19.[151,1436,356,704]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF89FFC3ECDE45E1B578FE1D" bold="true" box="[199,315,428,453]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">Remarks.</emphasis>
The original description gives the 
<typeStatus id="54B4E7F8FF89FFC3EED245E0B6B8FE1D" box="[715,763,429,453]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">type</typeStatus>
as a female, which is an error. However, there is no doubt that the specimen here regarded as the 
<typeStatus id="54B4E7F8FF89FFC3EE7B4582B687FE30" box="[610,708,463,488]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">holotype</typeStatus>
is correctly identified because it is the specimen illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E24ABFF89FFC3EC8E45B8B578FDD5" author="Zerny" box="[151,315,500,525]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" refString="Zerny, H. (1931 b) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Syntomiden. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 45, 1 - 27 + 1 plate." type="book chapter" year="1931" yearSuffix="b">
Zerny (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF89FFC3ECF045B9B567FDD5" box="[233,292,500,525]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" value="1931.0">1931</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
, and also it has a label with information provided in the original description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB0595AFF89FFC3ECDE465AB1CAFDA0" blockId="19.[151,1436,356,704]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">
The meaning of the first label is unknown. In the second, the holes made by the pin make it impossible to decipher what is written. It could mean that the specimen was illustrated by 
<collectingCountry id="F31819CAFF89FFC3EFF44670B072FD8C" box="[1005,1073,573,596]" name="Isle of Man" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">Mann</collectingCountry>
, who illustrated many European 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF89FFC3EC8E4612B55DFDA0" box="[151,286,607,632]" class="Insecta" family="Acanthopteroctetidae;Agathiphagidae;Alucitidae;Tineodidae;Axiidae;Axiidae;Calocarididae;Micheleidae;Strahlaxiidae;Bombycidae;Brahmaeidae;Carthaeidae;Endromidae;Eupterotidae;Lemoniidae;Mirinidae;Saturniidae;Sphingidae;Callidulidae;Choreutidae;Carposinidae;Copromorphidae;Cossidae;Dudgeoneidae;Drepanidae;Epicopeiidae;Epermeniidae;Eriocraniidae;Galacticidae;Agonoxenidae;Batrachedridae;Blastobasidae;Coleophoridae;Cosmopterigidae;Elachistidae;Ethmiidae;Gelechiidae;Holcopogonidae;Lecithoceridae;Metachandidae;Momphidae;Oecophoridae;Pterolonchidae;Scythrididae;Symmocidae;Geometridae;Sematuridae;Uraniidae;Bucculatricidae;Douglasiidae;Gracillariidae;Roeslerstammiidae;Hedylidae;Anomosetidae;Hepialidae;Neotheoridae;Palaeosetidae;Prototheoridae;Hesperiidae;Heterobathmiidae;Hyblaeidae;Immidae;Adelidae;Cecidosidae;Crinopterygidae;Heliozelidae;Incurvariidae;Prodoxidae;Anthelidae;Lasiocampidae;Lophocoronidae;Micropterigidae;Mimallonidae;Mnesarchaeidae;Neopseustidae;Nepticulidae;Opostegidae;Arctiidae;Doidae;Lymantriidae;Noctuidae;Nolidae;Notodontidae;Oenosandridae;Pantheidae;Palaephatidae;Lycaenidae;Nymphalidae;Papilionidae;Pieridae;Riodinidae;Pterophoridae;Crambidae;Pyralidae;Schreckensteiniidae;Brachodidae;Castniidae;Sesiidae;Simaethistidae;Thyrididae;Acrolophidae;Arrhenophanidae;Eriocottidae;Psychidae;Tineidae;Tischeriidae;Tortricidae;Urodidae;Whalleyanidae;Acrolepiidae;Bedelliidae;Glyphipterigidae;Heliodinidae;Lyonetiidae;Plutellidae;Yponomeutidae;Ypsolophidae;Aididae;Anomoeotidae;Chrysopolomidae;Cyclotornidae;Dalceridae;Epipyropidae;Heterogynidae;Himantopteridae;Lacturidae;Limacodidae;Megalopygidae;Somabrachyidae;Zygaenidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
(but mostly microlepidopterans), if the word reads “abgeb.” (abgebildet, which means “illustrated”).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB0595AFF89FFC3ECDE46C9B178FD18" blockId="19.[151,1436,356,704]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">
This species is remarkably similar to the illustration of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF89FFC3EF4A46C9B0A3FD44" authority="Cramer, 1779" authorityName="Cramer" authorityYear="1779" box="[851,1248,644,669]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Autochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="almon">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF89FFC3EF4A46C9B065FD45" box="[851,1062,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">Autochloris almon</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E24ABFF89FFC3E82146C9B09BFD44" author="Cramer" box="[1080,1240,644,668]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" refString="Cramer, P. (1779 - 1780) Papillons exotiques des trois parties du monde, L'Asie, L'Afrique et l'Amerique. Vol. 3. S. J. Baalde, Utrecht, Barthelemy Wild, 176 pp. + plates 193 - 288." type="book chapter" year="1779">
Cramer, 
<number id="3DC74B7DFF89FFC3E88646C9B09BFD44" box="[1183,1240,644,668]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" value="1779.0">1779</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
provided in the original description (plate 
<number id="3DC74B7DFF89FFC3EDA646E5B5AFFD18" box="[447,492,680,704]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" value="224.0">224</number>
, fig. F). It is unknown to us whether any of the 
<typeStatus id="54B4E7F8FF89FFC3E81846E5B07FFD18" box="[1025,1084,680,704]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF89FFC3E87846E5B085FD18" box="[1121,1222,679,704]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Autochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="almon">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF89FFC3E87846E5B085FD18" box="[1121,1222,679,704]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">A. almon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still exist.
</paragraph>
